folder: Central Park West & 100th Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Central Park West, lost to 100th Street.
(Before Reconstruction)
President Borough of Manhatten.
March 22, 1920.
title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 100th Street

folder: Central Park West & 100th Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Central Park West, west side, north from 100th Street. This photograph shows very clearly the havoc which the construction of the Eighth Avenue subway played with Central Park West. December, 1925.

Brown Brothers.
title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 100th Street

folder: 100th Street & Central Park West, Manhattan, NY
text:
100th Street, south side, west from Central Park West, to and including Columbus Ave.

October 23, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: 100th Street - Central Park West

folder: Central Park West & 100th Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
Central Park West, west side, at 101st Street, seen from Central Park near the 100th Street entrance. The tall new apartment house (1926) is on the N.W. corner of 101st Street. The buildings on the S.W. corner have been demolished.
October 23, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.


(2)
The same, a close view, showing principally the excavation at the S.W. corner and the houses on the north side of 101st Street. The small one, 19 West 101st Street, is the Community Hospital.
October 23, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
